# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values before running the project locally.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

---

## Required variables

### Supabase (required)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` | Your Supabase project URL, e.g. `https://<project-id>.supabase.co` |
| `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Supabase anonymous/public API key (safe to expose in the browser) |
| `VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID` | Supabase project identifier (used for CLI and management tasks) |

```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://<your-project-id>.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=<your-anon-key>
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=<your-project-id>
```

---

## Optional variables

### GitHub (optional)

Providing a token raises the GitHub API rate-limit from 60 req/h to 5 000 req/h
for the GitHub integration features.

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN` | GitHub Personal Access Token with `public_repo` scope |

```env
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_...
```

---

> **Security note**: Never commit `.env` to version control.  The `.gitignore`
> file already excludes it.  Only `VITE_*` prefixed variables are exposed to
> the browser bundle — keep any server-side secrets outside this prefix.
